        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20894",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This patch solves the problem.  It alters _httpRequest to properly parse OpenId messages and return the values they give back to whatever is calling it.  \n\nAdditionally, it falls back to sha1 encryption if sha256 fails, generating a new keypair in the process, just for safety's sake.  It should also alter all the other places that call _httpRequest.\n\nI've sort of hacked it together from our implementation, so I'm not quite sure if it's working, because I had to remove some key parts from our implementation before handing it over, but it kinda gives the idea of what the fix needs to happen in case. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-17T23:57:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-17T23:57:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20906",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Do you know a way to test the patch? (May be some OpenId provider which is affected by this bug)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-18T08:20:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-18T08:20:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20907",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, in 1.5.1 the Consumer fails on any 2.0 provider which doesn't support SHA-256.  This includes Yahoo, and I think every other 2.0 provider that we tried, though I can't recall any of the other ones at the moment.  Yahoo is the one I tested against, though, during which I discovered this bug and the url fragment bug.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-18T09:00:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-18T09:00:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20908",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oh yeah, I remembered now.  Beemba is another one, but I wouldn't test against them because they weren't fully up to spec, and my patch had to be loosened against spec to get them to work.\n\nhttp:\/\/openid.net\/specs\/openid-authentication-2_0.html#rfc.section.8.2.4\n\nThat's the relevant portion of the spec.  Beemba was returning unsupported-type but wasn't setting HTTP_STATUS to 400, which the spec requires.\n\nBecause these are really openid messages that are being passed back, I figured that I'd move their parsing outside of the _httpRequest function, since it seems like _associate() or verify() should be the ones interacting with the openid level of the protocol...  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=phuff",
                        "name": "phuff",
                        "displayName": "Paul Huff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-18T09:07:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-18T09:07:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20910",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tested with Yahoo.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
